{
  "local_port": 60348,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the scholarships an MBBS student in India?",
  "response": "MBBS students in India have access to various scholarships offered by government bodies, private organizations, and educational institutions to support their medical education. These scholarships aim to reduce financial burdens and encourage meritorious and needy students. Below are some notable scholarships available for MBBS students in India:\n\n---\n\n### **Government Scholarships**\n1. **National Scholarship Portal (NSP)**  \n   - Offers various scholarships for students pursuing professional courses like MBBS.  \n   - Examples: Central Sector Scheme of Scholarships, Post-Matric Scholarships, etc.\n\n2. **Ministry of Minority Affairs Scholarships**  \n   - **Pre-Matric Scholarship** and **Post-Matric Scholarship** for minority students (Muslims, Christians, Sikhs, Buddhists, Jains, and Parsis).  \n   - **Merit-Cum-Means Scholarship** for professional and technical courses.\n\n3. **Department of Empowerment of Persons with Disabilities (Divyangjan)**  \n   - Scholarships for students with disabilities pursuing MBBS.  \n   - Example: National Fellowship for Persons with Disabilities.\n\n4. **Central Sector Scheme of Scholarships for College and University Students**  \n   - For students with outstanding academic performance.\n\n5. **Indian Council of Medical Research (ICMR) Scholarships**  \n   - Offers scholarships for medical students interested in research.  \n   - **STS (Short-Term Studentship)** program for MBBS students.\n\n---\n\n### **State Government Scholarships**\n1. **Muktashree Scholarship (West Bengal)**  \n   - For economically backward students pursuing MBBS.\n\n2. **E-Kalyan Scholarship (Jharkhand)**  \n   - For SC/ST/OBC students in professional courses.\n\n3. **Post-Matric Scholarships (Various States)**  \n   - State-specific scholarships for students from reserved categories (SC/ST/OBC).\n\n4. **Karnataka State Scholarships**  \n   - For economically disadvantaged students pursuing medical education.\n\n---\n\n### **Private and Institutional Scholarships**\n1. **Dr. Reddy\u2019s Foundation Scholarship**  \n   - For meritorious and economically disadvantaged students pursuing MBBS.\n\n2. **K.C. Mahindra Scholarships for Post-Graduate Studies**  \n   - Offers financial aid to students in professional courses.\n\n3. **TATA Trust Scholarships**  \n   - For students from underprivileged backgrounds pursuing MBBS.\n\n4. **Narotam Sekhsaria Foundation Scholarship**  \n   - For meritorious students in professional courses, including MBBS.\n\n5. **LIC Golden Jubilee Scholarship**  \n   - For students from economically weaker sections pursuing professional courses.\n\n6. **Sun Pharma Foundation Scholarships**  \n   - For students pursuing medical and paramedical courses.\n\n7. **Fortis ESCORTS Heart Institute Scholarship**  \n   - For MBBS students specializing in cardiology.\n\n---\n\n### **Merit-Based Scholarships**\n1. **AICTE Pragati Scholarship for Girls**  \n   - For female students pursuing technical courses, including MBBS.\n\n2. **Sitaram Jindal Foundation Scholarship**  \n   - For meritorious students from economically weaker sections.\n\n3. **INSPIRE Scholarship**  \n   - For students excelling in academics (offered by the Department of Science and Technology).\n\n4. **Seth Jamnalal Bajaj Scholarships**  \n   - For students with outstanding academic records.\n\n---\n\n### **International Scholarships for MBBS Students**\n1. **Commonwealth Scholarship**  \n   - For Indian students pursuing higher education abroad.\n\n2. **Erasmus+ Scholarship**  \n   - For students interested in studying or researching abroad.\n\n3. **Rhodes Scholarship**  \n   - For students aspiring to study at the University of Oxford.\n\n---\n\n### **Fee Waivers and Financial Aid**\n- Many medical colleges in India offer fee waivers or financial aid to meritorious and economically disadvantaged students.  \n- Some colleges also provide hostel fee waivers or stipends.\n\n---\n\n### **How to Apply**\n- Check eligibility criteria for each scholarship.  \n- Prepare necessary documents, such as income certificates, academic records, and identity proofs.  \n- Apply online through official portals like the **National Scholarship Portal (NSP)** or the respective scholarship websites.\n\nFor more details, students can visit the **National Scholarship Portal** (https://scholarships.gov.in) or contact their college administration.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
